{
  "texts": [
    "We leave the investigation of a more precise separation of bias terms for future research.",
    "Discussion on the noise of the ϕ mapHere we analyze the impact of utilizing a Gaussian ϕ noise, as discussed in Section 4.2.",
    "Firstly, the equation is derived under the assumption that the lensed CMB is a Gaussian random field on the sphere, considering it as the primary source of error in the lensing reconstruction.",
    "However, higher-order noise biases N (p) L can also significantly affect the results, as highlighted in [43].",
    "This implies that we may be underestimating the reconstruction noise bias compared to practical lensing reconstruction, particularly at L > 1000 where NL dominates the reconstruction power spectrum."
  ]
}